cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with a large dataset of chest radiographs and investigates different approaches to using uncertainty labels for training convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of natural language processing techniques to design a labeler for detecting observations in radiology reports suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of medical imaging data suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
